HEADWORD: Thrombus
<hw>Throm"bus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Thrombi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ a lump, a
clot of blood.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A clot of
blood formed of a passage of a vessel and remaining at the site of
coagulation.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A tumor produced by the escape of
blood into the subcutaneous cellular tissue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

